HEADWORD: in-tray
<hw>in-tray</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a wood or metal receptacle placed on
a desk to hold incoming material requiring attention, especially
documents.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> in-box, in-basket.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

